TQMa6[QDL]/6UL/7[DS] Yocto integration test
===========================================

Supported boards
----------------

see Readme of TQ Sytems Layers (meta-tq)

Quick Start Guide
-----------------

Clone this repo using git clone --branch=<branch-name> --recurse-submodules <url>

current supported branche(s): krogoth

When switching branches keep in mind to keep the submodules in sync:

git submodule sync
git submodule update --init

To list supported machines:

LAYER=meta-tq
ls sources/${LAYER}/conf/machine/*.conf | sed s/\.conf//g | xargs -n1 basename

To help setting up an initial build space, use

MACHINE=<machine> source setup-environment <builddir> <config>

where config is: minimal | gui

This will use sources/template/conf/bblayers.conf.<config> as initial template
for your layer configuration.

After this step, everything is setup to build an image using bitbake.
To use a shared download directory, you can provide $DL_DIR via
~/.yocto/site.conf. This file - if available - will be automatically symlinked
into the conf dir of the build space.

To force a build of all supported machines in one of the configs, one can
use the CI helper script:

ci/build-all <builddir> <config>

